    "During World War I, while he served as artillery captain, his factories were destroyed.": [],
    "From 1919 onwards he chose a career in art history.": [],
    "He received his first initiation from his uncle, a collector of paintings.": [],
    "He spent much time in Belgium, where he studied under <a href=\"/hulindeloog\">Georges Nicolas Marie Hulin de Loo</a>.": [],
    "Michel's first publications (1920, 1923) dealt with civic and monastic monuments of Belgium.": [],
    "In 1924 he was appointed <em>attach\u00e9</em> at the department of paintings at the Louvre, where he specialized in Flemish painting.": [
        [
            3,
            7,
            [
                "1924,"
            ]
        ]
    ],
    "He published a volume on the Flemish school, <em>\u00c9cole flamande</em>, in <em>La peinture au Mus\u00e9e du Louvre</em>.": [],
    "With Hulin de Loo he authored, in 1927, the catalog of paintings of the Bruges art collector <a href=\"/renderse\">\u00c9mile Renders</a>, <em>Early Flemish Paintings in the Renders Collection at Bruges, Exhibited at the Belgian Exhibition, Burlington House, January, 1927</em>.": [
